article.headline: San Francisco 81, Portland 74
article.story: SAN FRANCISCO -- Michael Williams scored 18 points and Perris Blackwell added 12 points and 10 rebounds as San Francisco defeated Portland 81-74 on Thursday night. Cody Doolin had 14 points and Marko Petrovic 10 for the Dons (9-10, 3-1 West Coast Conference). Jared Stohl scored 19 points and Luke Sikma added 18 points and 10 rebounds for the Pilots (14-5, 2-2). San Francisco took control with a 12-0 surge over a period of 4:50 early in the second half. Williams and Doolin had a 3-pointer and layup each during the run, which gave the Dons a 46-31 advantage. Portland got no closer than five points afterward, and San Francisco sealed the win by making 10 free throws in the final 2:23.
